# 2p_combat — host. One comprehensive test that exercises movement,
# tracers, projectile sync, blood, decals, ragdoll, kill feed, and
# corpse interaction in a single ~10-second run.
#
# Pairs with 2p_combat.client.shot. Both spawn adjacent on the
# dummy platform (so they're in each other's view from t=0). Host
# walks left, fires a few aimed shots, takes return fire, dies
# around tick 500. Then the client (alive) walks past the corpse
# so decals and ragdoll positioning are visible from both views.
#
# What to look for in the screenshots:
#   - movement smooth in BOTH views (client view of host = host view
#     of host, modulo ~100 ms interp delay)
#   - tracers visible from BOTH shooters in BOTH views
#   - blood splatters at the same hit positions
#   - kill feed banner on both sides
#   - ragdoll body in same world position; decals match

window 1280 720
out build/shots/net/combat_host
network host 24081
name HostA

# Place host (slot 0) at world (2300, 1112) — on the dummy platform.
spawn_at 2300 1112
# Place client (slot 1) ~200 px right.
peer_spawn 1 2500 1112

# Aim at the client's chest the whole time.
aim 2500 1080

# Phase 1 (100-180): just settle.

# Phase 2 (180-260): walk left a bit (host moves away from client
# to test motion sync of moving remote mech).
at 180 press left
at 250 release left

# Phase 3 (260-380): fire a few single shots back at the client.
# Client retaliates harder so host loses the firefight.
at 280 tap fire
at 320 tap fire
at 360 tap fire

# Phase 4 (380+): host is now under heavy fire from client and dies.
# No more input — let the kill happen.

# Screenshots:
at 100 shot t100_spawn
at 220 shot t220_walking
at 320 shot t320_trading
at 440 shot t440_dying
at 580 shot t580_dead
at 750 shot t750_aftermath
at 900 end
